<font color="#FF0000">CLASS LASS, MORE COMMENTS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Oct 13 22:00:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Class Lass:<br><br>
One other point.<br><br>
Your questions have validity with someone returning from an ocean cruise to Tahiti. <br><br>
Combat screws up your mind. Combat screws up your body. Combat screws up your life.<br><br>
For the people sitting in their homes, and watching the 6pm news &quot;body count&quot; in the comfort of their recliners, might it not dawn on them that the conditions under which we served for their benefit were something considerably less desireable, mentally and physically?<br><br>
We were sent there for the benefit of this society. This society benefitted from our efforts. There was never any decompression. There was never any payback.<br><br>
As I said before, upon returning home, I felt like I had been beamed to a leper colony on an island in another country.<br><br>
Your academic smugness is deplorable.<br><br>
Art
